Package plugins

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BreachDepressions
    This tool can be used to pre-process a digital elevation model (DEM) prior to being used for hydrological analysis.
    BreachDepressionsFast
    This tool can be used as an alternative to Breach Depression, the results will not be as optimal as the solution offered by Breach Depression, however it is considerably faster to run.
    BreachPits
    This tool can be used to remove pits (single grid cells with no downslope neighbours) from a digital elevation model (DEM).
    BurnStreams
    This tool can be used to decrement the elevation values in a digital elevation model (DEM) along a defined stream network.
    CreateBlankOutletRaster
    This tool can be used to create a new raster, filled with NoData values, which possesses the same co-ordinates and demensions (i.e., rows and columns) as an existing base image.
    DownslopeFlowpathLength
    This tool can be used to calculate the downslope flowpath length from each grid cell in a raster to an outlet cell either at the edge of the grid or at the outlet point of a watershed.
    FillDepressions
    This tool can be used to fill all of the depressions in a digital elevation model (DEM) and to remove the flat areas.
    FillDepressionsPandD
    This tool can be used to fill all of the depressions in a digital elevation model (DEM) and to remove the flat areas and is most suitable for handling very large DEMs.
    FillPits
    This tool can be used to remove pits (single grid cells with no downslope neighbours) from a digital elevation model (DEM).
    FindNoFlowCells
    This tool can be used to find cells with undefined flow, meaning no valid flow direction based on the D8 flow direction algorithm.
    FindParallelFlow
    This tool can be used to find cells in a stream network grid that possess parallel flow directions based on an input D8 flow-pointer grid.
    FlowAccumD8
    This tool is used to generate a flow accumulation raster using the simple D8 (O'Callaghan and Mark, 1984) algorithm.
    FlowAccumDinf
    This tool is used to generate a flow accumulation grid (i.e., contributing area) using the D-infinity algorithm (Tarboton, 1997).
    FlowAccumFD8
    This tool is used to generate a flow accumulation grid (i.e., contributing area) using the FD8 algorithm (Freeman, 1991).
    FlowPointerD8
    This tool is used to generate a flow pointer grid using the simple D8 (O'Callaghan and Mark, 1984) algorithm.
    FlowPointerDinf
    This tool is used to generate a flow pointer grid (i.e., flow direction) using the D-infinity (Tarboton, 1997) algorithm.
    FlowPointerFD8
    This tool is used to generate a flow pointer grid (i.e., flow direction) using the FD8 (Freeman, 1991) algorithm.
    FlowPointerRho8
    This tool is used to generate a flow pointer grid (i.e., flow direction) using the stochastic Rho8 (Fairfield and Leymarie, 1991) algorithm.
    Hillslopes
    This tool will identify the hillslopes associated with a user-specified stream network.
    Isobasin
    This tool can be used to divide a landscape into a group of nearly equal-sized watersheds, known as isobasins.
    JensonSnapPourPoints
    The Jenson Snap Pour Points tool can be used to move the location of pour points (i.e., outlets used in a watershedding operation) to the nearest stream grid cell within a specified distance.
    MassFluxD8
    This tool can be used to perform a mass flux calculation using DEM-based surface flow-routing techniques.
    MassFluxDinf
    This tool can be used to perform a mass flux calculation using DEM-based surface flow-routing techniques.
    NumInflowingNeighbours
    This tool calculates the number of inflowing neighbours for each grid cell in a raster file.
    SnapPourPoints
    The Snap Pour Points tool can be used to move the location of pour points (i.e., outlets used in a watershedding operation) to the location coincident with the highest flow accumulation value within a specified distance.
    StrahlerOrderBasins
    This tool will identify the catchment areas of each Horton-Strahler stream order link in a user-specified stream network.
    Subbasins
    This tool will identify the catchment areas to each link in a user-specified stream network i.e., the network's sub-basins
    WallWatershed
    This tool is used to increment the elevations in a digital elevation model (DEM) along the boundaries of a watershed polygon.
    Watershed
    This tool will perform a watershedding operation based on a group of specified pour points i.e., outlets or target cells.
